column3: A straight and single trunked Palm Tree can grow up to 30m tall but normally between 10 to 15m in height. Trunk is green when young; grey coloured with white leaf scars when they're old. Leaves are even-pinnately with 30 to 50 lanceolate-shaped leaflets.

The coconut palm is a large palm that grows up to 30m tall. It has leaves that are 4–6 m long. The term coconut refers to the fruit of the coconut palm. Coconut milk is also used in many drinks. Coconut oil is often used in food and soaps.

Saltbush species are used as food plants by the larvaes. Saltbush plants offer opportunities to hide and hunt in habitat that is otherwise often quite barren. They can also be used to prevent soil erosion in coastal ares.
Thyme is an aromatic perennial evergreen herb with culinary; medicinal and ornamental uses. Thyme is best cultivated in a hot; sunny location with well-drained soil.

The banana plant is the largest herbaceous flowering plant. Plants are normally tall and fairly sturdy and are often mistaken for trees but what appears to be a trunk is actually a "false stem". The banana fruits develop from the banana heart in a large hanging cluster made up of tiers (called "hands") with up to 20 fruit to a tier.

Spruces are large trees; from about 20 to 60 m tall when mature and can be distinguished by their whorled branches and conical form. The leaves of spruces are attached singly to the branches in a spiral fashion each needle on a small peg-like structure. The needles are shed when 4–10 years old; leaving the branches rough with the retained pegs. Spruces are used as food plants by the larvae of some Lepidoptera (Butterfly) species.
Alders are deciduous and the leaves are alternate; simple and serrated. They are mainly wind-pollinated but also visited by bees to a small extent.

Rubber Tree is a tall deciduous tree growing to a height of up to 43 m in the wild but cultivated trees are usually much smaller because drawing off the latex restricts the growth of the tree. The trunk is cylindrical and may have a swollen; bottle-shaped base.
Typically the mahogany tree can grow up to 45m high; and 4m in diameter. But the average diameter is only about 1.5m feet. Often the first limb is over 15m up.

Ebony is dense enough to sink in water. It is finely-textured and has a very smooth finish when polished; making it valuable as an ornamental wood. Modern uses are largely restricted to small items and musical instrument parts.

Cedar trees can grow up to 30–40 m (occasionally 60 m) tall with spicy-resinous scented wood; thick ridged or square-cracked bark and broad; level branches. The leaves are evergreen; needle-like and 8–60 mm long.
Pine trees are evergreen and can grow up to 80 m tall with the majority of species reaching 15–45m tall. Pines are long-lived and typically reach ages of 100–1.000 years; some even more.

Oaks have spirally arranged leaves. In spring; a single oak tree produces both male flowers and small female flowers. The fruit is a nut called an acorn. Each acorn contains 1-3 seeds and takes 6–18 months to mature.

The needles are shed when 4–10 years old; leaving the branches rough with the retained pegs. Spruces are used as food plants by the larvae of some Lepidoptera (Butterfly) species.

They are large trees; reaching heights of 10–80m tall with trunk diameters of 0.5–4m when mature. Firs can be distinguished from other members of the pine family by the unique attachment of their needle-like leaves and by their different cones.

Cedrus trees can grow up to 30–40 m (occasionally 60 m) tall with spicy-resinous scented wood; thick ridged or square-cracked bark and broad; level branches. The leaves are evergreen; needle-like and 8–60 mm long.

They are large trees; reaching heights of 10–80m tall with trunk diameters of 0.5–4m when mature. Firs can be distinguished from other members of the pine family by the unique attachment of their needle-like leaves and by their different cones.

Willows are low-growing or creeping shrubs which rarely exceeds 6 cm in height; though it spreads widely across the ground. The leaves are typically elongated but may also be round to oval; frequently with serrated edges.

They live in extremely dry environments. Cactus have a variety of uses: many species are used as ornamental plants; others are grown for forage; and others for food (particularly their fruit). Great majority of them has no leaves. Photosynthesis takes place in the stems

Baobabs reach heights of 5 to 30m and have trunk diameters of 7 to 11m. There are known specimens that is older than 1000 years. The fruit has a velvety shell and is about the size of a coconut; weighing about 1.5 kilograms. It has an acidic tart flavor.

Date Tree is a flowering plant species in the palm family. Cultivated for its edible sweet fruit. Date trees typically reach about 21–23 metres in height; growing singly or forming a clump with several stems from a single root system. Date fruits (dates) are oval-cylindrical; 3–7 cm long and about 2.5 cm in diameter; ranging from bright red to bright yellow in color; depending on variety. They are very sweet; containing about 75 percent of sugar when dried.

Desert Sage is a woody subshrub reaching up to 1m in height and width. The grey-green leaves are narrow and lanceolate are tapered at the base and rounded at the tip and have a smooth and round margin. They are generally basal; and about 1–3 cm long. They have an intense but pleasant; mildly intoxicating minty aroma; with the scent released when the foliage is handled or crushed.
In its native climes this slow-growing tree can reach up to 18m high and 0.9m in stem diameter. The tree aloe is often used as an ornamental plant.

Acacia is a common food source and host plant for butterflies. They can be found both thorned and thornless. Its flowers are yellow and aromatic.

This tall succulent tree with green round-like branches resembling a balloon is 6–8 meters tall. Its trunk is thick. Milky latex of the tree is extremely poisonous and can cause blindness; severe skin irritation and poisoning (when ingested) with humans and animals. However when properly used this plant can serve as purgative or drug curing ulcers.
A mature eucalyptus may take the form of a low shrub or a very large tree. Nearly all eucalyptus are evergreen.
